  "active_lock_reason": "resolved",
  "body": "There seems to be an issue wherein `hardhat` is not catching errors that are thrown on-chain.\r\n\r\nIf we have the following function:\r\n\r\n```\r\n    function greet(bytes calldata) external pure returns (uint256) {\r\n        return 0;\r\n    }\r\n```\r\n\r\nand perform the following call:\r\n\r\n```\r\nconst resp = await contract.greet(1);\r\n```\r\n\r\nThen the call should fail with an `INVALID ARGUMENT`; however, it does not.\r\n\r\n[Minimal Reproducible Example Repository](https://github.com/lostarchitect/hardhat-bug)\r\n",
